                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular, by a well-trained hand.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>The handwriting is similar to that of Ms.
                           <ref target="ESqqm005" type="mss">QQM-005</ref>.<date>Late 15th - first half of the 16th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Incipits and headings of the texts; numbers and
                           titles of the chapters written in the margins; short postscripts to the
                           Gospels; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic
                           numerals of the Eusebian sections (in the margins); chi rho; crux
                           ansata.
 
 The incipits of the Gospels are written alternately in
                           red and black lines (s. fols. 1r, 49r, 73r, 123r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
